WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.388
Captain?

00:00:02.725 --> 00:00:03.975
I'm coming in, Captain.

00:00:05.686 --> 00:00:06.687
Excuse me...

00:00:10.899 --> 00:00:11.899
Captain...

00:00:12.150 --> 00:00:13.609
If you were in here,
you could have at least answered—

00:00:13.609 --> 00:00:14.820
Nanao...

00:00:17.448 --> 00:00:20.283
We might have to say goodbye.

00:00:21.534 --> 00:00:22.536
What?

00:00:22.744 --> 00:00:25.664
"MESSAGE"

00:00:25.664 --> 00:00:30.753
"APPOINTING SHUNSUI JIRO
SAKURANOSUKE KYORAKU
AS HEAD CAPTAIN
AND SQUAD 1 CAPTAIN"

00:00:34.088 --> 00:00:35.466
Give me a break...

00:00:57.195 --> 00:01:01.950
<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:01:02.075 --> 00:01:07.164
<i>At my wit's end, I feel a growing frustration</i>

00:01:07.581 --> 00:01:12.001
<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:01:12.335 --> 00:01:15.756
<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:01:16.215 --> 00:01:22.096
<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:01:22.387 --> 00:01:25.307
<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:01:26.516 --> 00:01:31.522
<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:01:31.772 --> 00:01:34.399
<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:01:34.525 --> 00:01:39.028
<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:01:39.153 --> 00:01:41.864
<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:01:41.989 --> 00:01:46.828
<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:01:46.953 --> 00:01:49.373
<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:01:49.498 --> 00:01:51.375
<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:55.128
<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:01:55.419 --> 00:01:59.174
<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:01:59.299 --> 00:02:02.260
<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:06.973
BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:02:19.819 --> 00:02:22.948
"KIRINDEN"

00:02:22.948 --> 00:02:23.866
- 91...92...
- 91...92...

00:02:23.991 --> 00:02:25.908
- 93...
- 93...

00:02:26.242 --> 00:02:27.786
- 94—
- 94...

00:02:29.955 --> 00:02:32.039
You failed, you moron!

00:02:32.206 --> 00:02:34.418
Didn't your parents
teach you as a kid?

00:02:34.877 --> 00:02:36.502
You're not supposed to
get out of a bath

00:02:36.502 --> 00:02:38.254
until you've finished
counting up to 100!

00:02:38.588 --> 00:02:40.841
What kind of parent
makes their kid count to 100

00:02:40.841 --> 00:02:42.717
while their head's underwater?!

00:02:42.717 --> 00:02:44.343
Quit your whining!

00:02:44.677 --> 00:02:46.013
Kazuo!
Kazuhiro!

00:02:46.013 --> 00:02:47.306
- Yessir!
- Come on, Bro!

00:02:47.931 --> 00:02:50.016
Nothing personal, boy!

00:02:51.018 --> 00:02:52.477
Damn you, boy!

00:02:52.477 --> 00:02:53.729
It's Ichigo!

00:02:55.438 --> 00:02:56.439
Wait.

00:03:03.447 --> 00:03:04.823
What the hell was that for?!

00:03:04.823 --> 00:03:06.116
You're healed.

00:03:09.703 --> 00:03:12.330
If you weren't,
that would have killed you.

00:03:12.914 --> 00:03:15.250
Look.
Your wounds are gone.

00:03:15.250 --> 00:03:17.794
"KIRINDEN"

00:03:18.002 --> 00:03:20.129
You finished
what you came here to do.

00:03:20.713 --> 00:03:23.008
I'll prepare for you
to go to the next place.

00:03:23.592 --> 00:03:24.592
The next place?

00:03:24.759 --> 00:03:25.843
Wait up...!

00:03:28.055 --> 00:03:29.181
I'm coming with you.

00:03:29.889 --> 00:03:31.807
Renji!
Don't be silly.

00:03:31.807 --> 00:03:32.935
You're still...

00:03:48.699 --> 00:03:49.700
Well?

00:03:49.951 --> 00:03:51.912
You didn't send me flying.

00:03:57.584 --> 00:03:58.794
Fine.

00:03:58.794 --> 00:04:01.545
If you can withstand my punch,
you're probably all right.

00:04:02.463 --> 00:04:03.464
Go.

00:04:04.173 --> 00:04:05.175
Thanks!

00:04:07.009 --> 00:04:08.512
- Ready...
- Go!

00:04:10.639 --> 00:04:14.892
Aren't there any other ways of
getting around this place?!

00:04:15.644 --> 00:04:16.644
There they go...

00:04:17.646 --> 00:04:18.939
Kazuo!
Kazuhiro!

00:04:20.690 --> 00:04:22.192
Thanks for the hard work.

00:04:22.483 --> 00:04:23.485
You can take those off now.

00:04:23.776 --> 00:04:24.778
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

00:04:30.033 --> 00:04:31.033
That was close...

00:04:31.285 --> 00:04:33.120
If it weren't for
these protective bathing robes

00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:34.495
made of super spiritual threads,

00:04:34.745 --> 00:04:35.872
the extreme recovery would have

00:04:35.872 --> 00:04:37.915
caused our bodies to erode
and rupture.

00:04:37.915 --> 00:04:41.043
Yet those boys were able to soak in
Master Tenjiro's White Bone Hell

00:04:41.043 --> 00:04:43.754
and Blood Pond Hell naked
as if it was nothing...

00:04:44.338 --> 00:04:46.382
Unbelievable...

00:04:47.216 --> 00:04:48.218
Yeah.

00:04:48.759 --> 00:04:51.846
I saw their potential, but they
went beyond my expectations.

00:04:52.139 --> 00:04:53.932
Especially that Ichigo kid.

00:04:55.016 --> 00:04:57.810
When that punk took my strike,

00:04:57.978 --> 00:05:01.857
he reflexively struck my fist
and fractured it.

00:05:02.858 --> 00:05:03.858
My word...

00:05:04.108 --> 00:05:06.862
People used to call me
"Lightning Fast Tenjiro"

00:05:06.862 --> 00:05:08.612
for my Hoho skills...

00:05:09.572 --> 00:05:12.658
Pretty sure I haven't
lost my touch yet...

00:05:13.951 --> 00:05:16.704
That kid is really something...

00:05:18.247 --> 00:05:20.666
I can see why the Soul King
is so into him...

00:05:22.461 --> 00:05:24.129
<i>Two</i> lieutenants?!

00:05:24.129 --> 00:05:25.672
CENTRAL 46
UNDERGROUND ASSEMBLY HALL Yes.

00:05:25.672 --> 00:05:28.550
CENTRAL 46
UNDERGROUND ASSEMBLY HALL
Third Seat Okikiba
knows how to manage Squad 1...

00:05:28.550 --> 00:05:29.134
CENTRAL 46
UNDERGROUND ASSEMBLY HALL
while Lieutenant Ise
knows how to handle me.

00:05:29.134 --> 00:05:32.846
while Lieutenant Ise
knows how to handle me.

00:05:33.555 --> 00:05:36.350
They will both fulfill the duties
of assisting me.

00:05:36.682 --> 00:05:37.809
No!
This is unacceptable—

00:05:37.809 --> 00:05:39.978
"The power to appoint someone
to lieutenant "

00:05:39.978 --> 00:05:41.480
"lies with their squad captain."

00:05:42.189 --> 00:05:45.983
Your people decided that, remember?

00:05:49.737 --> 00:05:54.951
Now then, may I proceed with
my first task as head captain?

00:06:00.956 --> 00:06:04.211
I intend to teach
Kenpachi Zaraki Zanjutsu.

00:06:04.586 --> 00:06:05.629
- What?!
- What?!

00:06:06.713 --> 00:06:09.925
Captain Kuchiki and the others
went to the Royal Palace,

00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:12.343
but there's no guarantee
they'll return safely.

00:06:13.136 --> 00:06:15.721
Captain Zaraki is
an important asset in battle.

00:06:15.930 --> 00:06:18.182
We cannot leave him as he is now.

00:06:18.641 --> 00:06:19.642
No!

00:06:19.767 --> 00:06:21.853
If he becomes more powerful
than he is now,

00:06:21.853 --> 00:06:24.605
we won't be able to stop him
if he revolts!

00:06:24.814 --> 00:06:27.733
Have you forgotten
we urged Genryusai

00:06:27.733 --> 00:06:30.069
to stop teaching him Kendo
after only a day?!

00:06:30.487 --> 00:06:31.987
Then what do you suggest we do?

00:06:32.488 --> 00:06:33.490
In its current state,

00:06:33.490 --> 00:06:36.367
the Soul Society won't be able to
withstand the next invasion.

00:06:37.285 --> 00:06:40.663
Will any of you be able to
protect yourselves?

00:06:49.130 --> 00:06:51.966
It seems like
I've been given permission.

00:06:54.427 --> 00:06:55.428
Come on in.

00:06:56.137 --> 00:06:58.889
I'd like you to handle this matter
concerning Captain Zaraki.

00:07:05.980 --> 00:07:07.690
Captain Unohana...

00:07:08.692 --> 00:07:09.692
Or should I say...

00:07:11.235 --> 00:07:13.028
The First Kenpachi...

00:07:13.988 --> 00:07:15.615
Yachiru Unohana.

00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:22.204
You go on the bottom!

00:07:22.204 --> 00:07:26.125
<i>My</i> injuries were worse than yours!
So you go!

00:07:26.125 --> 00:07:29.670
You're all healed up!
What are you, a wuss?

00:07:29.670 --> 00:07:31.423
You're one to talk!
You damn—

00:07:34.341 --> 00:07:35.343
Huh?

00:07:38.555 --> 00:07:41.432
I couldn't have been found
at a worse time!

00:07:41.432 --> 00:07:48.523
GATONDEN - LANDING AREA
Good grief...

00:07:48.899 --> 00:07:51.860
Crashing from that height
after my body just healed

00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:53.319
- would have been awful.
- Hey, get back here!

00:07:53.612 --> 00:07:55.237
It would only have been
awful for you.

00:07:55.697 --> 00:07:58.949
I would have been able to
land safely using a breakfall.

00:07:58.949 --> 00:08:00.117
What was that?

00:08:00.117 --> 00:08:01.952
- I bet you can't do that, can you?
- Screw you...

00:08:01.952 --> 00:08:04.038
Welcome!

00:08:04.497 --> 00:08:07.459
I'm glad you came,
Ichigo and Renji!

00:08:08.043 --> 00:08:10.045
Welcome to my Gatonden!

00:08:10.336 --> 00:08:11.879
I'm gonna take good care
of both of you!

00:08:14.007 --> 00:08:15.007
Seriously...!

00:08:16.134 --> 00:08:19.053
Is there no one but idiots
in this place?!

00:08:21.972 --> 00:08:23.892
Hup, hup,

00:08:23.892 --> 00:08:26.477
hup, hup,
hup, hup, hup!

00:08:26.477 --> 00:08:27.562
GATONDEN - KITCHEN AREA
hup, hup,
hup, hup, hup!

00:08:27.562 --> 00:08:29.188
GATONDEN - KITCHEN AREA
Become tastier!

00:08:29.188 --> 00:08:31.232
GATONDEN - KITCHEN AREA
And... here you go!

00:08:36.238 --> 00:08:40.866
GATONDEN - MAIN HALL

00:08:40.866 --> 00:08:42.660
When she said she was going to
take care of us...

00:08:42.869 --> 00:08:46.081
I thought she meant it as
whipping us into shape, but...

00:08:46.873 --> 00:08:48.958
Looks like she really meant
what she said...

00:08:49.833 --> 00:08:51.378
This is amazing!

00:08:51.878 --> 00:08:52.836
Come on, let's eat!

00:08:52.836 --> 00:08:55.756
I was super hungry!

00:08:55.756 --> 00:08:56.841
Wait, you idiot!

00:08:57.091 --> 00:09:00.010
There's no way she'd serve us
this food for no reason!

00:09:00.261 --> 00:09:02.764
I bet it's an excuse to start
some ridiculous form of training!

00:09:02.764 --> 00:09:04.099
My, oh, my...

00:09:04.474 --> 00:09:09.144
Seems you grew up distrustful
thanks to Kisuke Urahara.

00:09:10.563 --> 00:09:12.356
There's no need to worry!

00:09:12.899 --> 00:09:15.110
This Gatonden is a palace of food.

00:09:16.027 --> 00:09:20.115
My job is to ensure
your bellies are full!

00:09:20.615 --> 00:09:25.245
And your job is to
stuff your bellies!

00:09:25.662 --> 00:09:27.455
Now eat up!

00:09:27.788 --> 00:09:30.166
I'm sure you must be
incredibly hungry!

00:09:34.629 --> 00:09:36.880
- Let's dig in!
- Let's dig in!

00:09:47.182 --> 00:09:48.350
Mm-hm.

00:09:48.893 --> 00:09:50.519
What a healthy appetite.

00:09:50.687 --> 00:09:53.023
I'll go make dessert!

00:09:54.316 --> 00:09:56.735
So good!
I can't stop eating!

00:09:57.027 --> 00:09:58.110
I can...

00:09:58.445 --> 00:10:02.032
I'm finding some weird stuff
mixed in from time to time...

00:10:02.365 --> 00:10:04.075
What the hell is this?

00:10:08.413 --> 00:10:09.413
Unbelievable...

00:10:09.788 --> 00:10:13.835
It looks grotesque,
but surprisingly tastes awesome!

00:10:13.835 --> 00:10:16.171
It has an awesome texture
to it too!

00:10:16.171 --> 00:10:18.380
And the way the awesome aroma
spreads through your mouth

00:10:18.380 --> 00:10:19.883
is so awesome!

00:10:19.883 --> 00:10:20.966
Stop.

00:10:20.966 --> 00:10:24.386
Hearing your horrible food critique
is ruining my meal.

00:10:31.644 --> 00:10:33.480
What?
Are you done already?

00:10:33.647 --> 00:10:34.938
I can still eat more.

00:10:35.273 --> 00:10:37.859
You idiot!
I can totally keep going!

00:10:38.485 --> 00:10:39.943
I'm just taking a break!

00:10:49.453 --> 00:10:50.455
Hey, Renji...

00:10:51.998 --> 00:10:54.918
Should we... really be doing this?

00:10:57.294 --> 00:10:59.004
Everyone in the Seireitei

00:10:59.004 --> 00:11:01.841
is training right now
to prepare for the next battle...

00:11:02.424 --> 00:11:05.886
While we're here taking baths,
eating food,

00:11:06.303 --> 00:11:07.806
and just fooling around...

00:11:08.847 --> 00:11:10.683
Will doing this really...

00:11:11.809 --> 00:11:14.019
make us strong enough
for the next battle?

00:11:18.524 --> 00:11:19.734
Are you really that dumb?

00:11:20.110 --> 00:11:22.986
- What?!
- We were both injured in battle.

00:11:23.278 --> 00:11:25.990
So we took a bath
to heal our wounds.

00:11:26.198 --> 00:11:27.951
Once our wounds healed,
we got hungry.

00:11:28.618 --> 00:11:30.285
That's why we're eating now.

00:11:31.037 --> 00:11:32.580
It all makes perfect sense.

00:11:33.163 --> 00:11:34.916
We are building up our strength

00:11:34.916 --> 00:11:37.168
to prepare for the tough training
that lies ahead.

00:11:38.336 --> 00:11:39.294
Wow...

00:11:39.921 --> 00:11:41.755
You actually make a good point
once in a while.

00:11:42.005 --> 00:11:42.923
Shut up!

00:11:42.923 --> 00:11:44.926
If you agree, then eat more!

00:11:45.259 --> 00:11:46.344
You can still keep going,
can't you?!

00:11:46.594 --> 00:11:47.636
Of course, I can!

00:11:50.097 --> 00:11:51.432
I'm going to eat more than you!

00:11:51.432 --> 00:11:52.975
Dream on!
I'm going to—

00:11:55.352 --> 00:11:57.147
Renji is right!

00:11:57.397 --> 00:12:00.482
I guess it's only natural
for a lieutenant to figure it out!

00:12:01.192 --> 00:12:04.486
You fully understood
what I was saying!

00:12:07.072 --> 00:12:08.158
That's right!

00:12:08.450 --> 00:12:09.951
What we're doing right now

00:12:09.951 --> 00:12:13.830
is no different than getting ready
for any other training.

00:12:14.748 --> 00:12:15.789
The only difference is,

00:12:15.789 --> 00:12:18.793
it's being done
on a Soul King scale.

00:12:20.211 --> 00:12:23.590
Our rituals are packed with
the Soul King's power

00:12:23.590 --> 00:12:26.926
and the million-year history
of the Soul Society.

00:12:27.844 --> 00:12:30.221
It's on a whole other level
from the healing and diet

00:12:30.221 --> 00:12:32.182
that you know in the Seireitei.

00:12:32.932 --> 00:12:35.018
Now focus on rebuilding your body.

00:12:35.143 --> 00:12:37.144
So you don't die
in the next palace.

00:12:38.062 --> 00:12:41.732
Now that you understand,
have some dessert!

00:12:43.025 --> 00:12:44.027
Wh...

00:12:44.402 --> 00:12:45.986
- Who are you?!
- Who are you?!

00:12:47.780 --> 00:12:48.822
Oh, this?

00:12:48.822 --> 00:12:51.533
I use up all my Spiritual Pressure
when I cook.

00:12:51.868 --> 00:12:55.120
So after I'm done cooking,
I always lose a lot of weight.

00:12:56.331 --> 00:12:59.208
"GRAIN KING" - KIRIO HIKIFUNE

00:13:02.711 --> 00:13:04.087
Ichigo, Renji.

00:13:05.005 --> 00:13:06.006
Be careful out there.

00:13:06.883 --> 00:13:09.802
Remember how I told you
our Ritual was

00:13:09.802 --> 00:13:12.429
packed with the history
of the Soul Society?

00:13:13.556 --> 00:13:15.808
Every one of us in Squad Zero

00:13:15.808 --> 00:13:19.269
has created something
in the Soul Society...

00:13:19.895 --> 00:13:22.481
And those who are
recognized as being

00:13:22.481 --> 00:13:25.317
the history of the Soul Society
itself by the Soul King

00:13:25.317 --> 00:13:26.985
are allowed to join our squad.

00:13:27.946 --> 00:13:31.032
What I've created
was a temporary soul

00:13:31.032 --> 00:13:33.283
and the technology
to place it into a body.

00:13:34.409 --> 00:13:38.831
The concept of Gikon did not exist
until I created a temporary soul.

00:13:39.456 --> 00:13:44.419
And part of that concept was
applied to create Soul Candies.

00:13:45.879 --> 00:13:48.799
The essence of Gikon
is to increase one's level of power

00:13:48.799 --> 00:13:51.802
by placing a completely foreign
Spiritual Pressure

00:13:51.802 --> 00:13:53.554
into your own body.

00:13:54.054 --> 00:13:56.432
The food you ate
was filled with that essence.

00:13:57.057 --> 00:13:59.394
Your bodies should now be
containing Spiritual Pressure

00:13:59.394 --> 00:14:01.770
that is nothing like
you've felt before.

00:14:03.063 --> 00:14:05.482
If you can sense that
even a little, then good.

00:14:06.234 --> 00:14:07.235
That said...

00:14:07.610 --> 00:14:09.111
I still want you
to go with caution.

00:14:11.280 --> 00:14:15.743
The one in the next palace
is totally unpredictable.

00:14:16.952 --> 00:14:19.998
Your next stop is Hoohden,
where Oh-Etsu Nimaiya resides...

00:14:21.624 --> 00:14:24.043
He is the man
who created Zanpakuto.

00:14:46.857 --> 00:14:49.235
THE CENTRAL UNDERGROUND
GREAT PRISON

00:14:55.158 --> 00:15:02.164
LOWEST LEVEL - "MUKEN"

00:15:15.886 --> 00:15:19.097
This is a rather grandiose stage,
isn't it?

00:15:20.099 --> 00:15:23.311
I'm surprised you were able to
get permission to use this place.

00:15:24.770 --> 00:15:26.188
It was the Head Captain's orders.

00:15:27.815 --> 00:15:31.152
As its name suggests,
Muken is completely closed off...

00:15:31.903 --> 00:15:34.947
and infinitely large...

00:15:35.782 --> 00:15:39.034
Thus, it was decided that
this was the only place

00:15:39.034 --> 00:15:42.120
suitable for you
to freely swing your sword.

00:15:43.288 --> 00:15:44.539
Otherwise,

00:15:44.539 --> 00:15:49.836
they never would have allowed us
non-criminals to enter this space.

00:15:52.798 --> 00:15:54.634
"Non-criminals"?

00:15:54.759 --> 00:15:56.219
Look who's talking.

00:15:56.927 --> 00:16:00.807
If you and I weren't powerful,
we'd just be ordinary criminals!

00:16:10.357 --> 00:16:12.485
Right now, you have no power.

00:16:13.152 --> 00:16:14.445
I suggested this place

00:16:14.445 --> 00:16:17.865
because I felt
you would fit in perfectly here.

00:16:18.323 --> 00:16:20.826
Yeah, that's what I figured.

00:16:21.869 --> 00:16:23.245
Fine by me.

00:16:23.870 --> 00:16:26.206
Win as a captain,
or lose as a criminal...

00:16:26.916 --> 00:16:29.001
Doesn't matter if I live or die
fighting you.

00:16:29.251 --> 00:16:31.169
It's still going to be
an eternal hell.

00:16:32.379 --> 00:16:34.966
You're quite talkative today,
aren't you?

00:16:37.342 --> 00:16:39.971
I like you better
when you're quiet.

00:16:41.054 --> 00:16:42.932
Whenever I hear your voice,

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:48.980
the single scar you gave me
begins to ache.

00:16:49.397 --> 00:16:50.522
Shut up.

00:16:50.772 --> 00:16:52.900
Don't think you're the only one...

00:16:52.900 --> 00:16:54.943
who's got an aching scar!

00:17:01.366 --> 00:17:02.951
Yachiru Unohana...

00:17:03.661 --> 00:17:04.996
The original
Thirteen Court Guard Squads,

00:17:04.996 --> 00:17:06.705
said to be
the strongest in history...

00:17:07.039 --> 00:17:09.709
She served as
the captain of Squad 11

00:17:09.709 --> 00:17:12.795
and created the basis
of what Squad 11 is today.

00:17:13.921 --> 00:17:16.923
Before being appointed as a captain
by Old Man Yama,

00:17:17.090 --> 00:17:20.678
she was the most notorious criminal
in the history of the Soul Society.

00:17:21.136 --> 00:17:24.057
To show her mastery
of countless styles

00:17:24.057 --> 00:17:26.933
and her complete proficiency
of the blade,

00:17:27.309 --> 00:17:30.229
she gave herself the name
"Yachiru (Eight Thousand Styles)"...

00:17:33.691 --> 00:17:37.653
I'm sorry I called it
a Zanjutsu lesson...

00:17:40.030 --> 00:17:43.451
Once you and Captain Zaraki
cross blades...

00:17:47.829 --> 00:17:49.749
one of you will have to die.

00:17:50.583 --> 00:17:52.626
I knew that...

00:18:01.469 --> 00:18:04.471
"TO ISANE"

00:18:22.949 --> 00:18:23.950
Kenny...

00:18:25.867 --> 00:18:27.702
Captain Unohana...

00:18:58.776 --> 00:19:03.405
I commend you for removing
your eyepatch from the start.

00:19:04.030 --> 00:19:08.618
But even if you remove it,
that is the extent of your power.

00:19:18.336 --> 00:19:19.337
So weak...

00:19:27.305 --> 00:19:29.807
I can't believe someone
swinging a sword with one arm,

00:19:29.807 --> 00:19:32.602
wouldn't make use
of their other arm...

00:19:33.603 --> 00:19:36.939
I can't imagine
you're enjoying this fight.

00:19:38.023 --> 00:19:39.317
And what about you?

00:19:39.817 --> 00:19:42.278
To think you'd resort to using
a cheap trick like this

00:19:42.278 --> 00:19:44.238
to wound me.

00:19:45.405 --> 00:19:47.991
You've changed quite a bit...

00:19:50.452 --> 00:19:52.913
...from the person I admired!

00:19:52.913 --> 00:19:56.541
How dare you admire
the enemy amid battle!

00:20:09.971 --> 00:20:12.724
I haven't changed at all.

00:20:13.976 --> 00:20:16.311
But when I last fought you...

00:20:16.938 --> 00:20:21.067
I simply did not have the leeway to
use such cheap tricks against you.

00:20:22.984 --> 00:20:23.986
Are you saying...

00:20:24.612 --> 00:20:26.821
that I've gotten weaker?

00:20:33.496 --> 00:20:35.914
I admired you...

00:20:37.875 --> 00:20:39.460
Trees, bugs, people...

00:20:39.919 --> 00:20:41.796
No matter what I cut,
it was all the same.

00:20:42.171 --> 00:20:43.338
It was boring...

00:20:43.923 --> 00:20:47.759
It was no different from swinging
a sword while alone in the dark.

00:20:49.345 --> 00:20:52.847
Fighting you
was the first time I felt fear.

00:20:54.057 --> 00:20:56.894
I felt the joy of battle
for the first time.

00:20:57.394 --> 00:21:00.105
I wanted to fight just like you.

00:21:01.190 --> 00:21:02.817
But you're saying...

00:21:07.529 --> 00:21:13.493
...I'm going to die here...
without ever beating you?!

00:21:33.263 --> 00:21:34.682
Damn it...

00:21:41.314 --> 00:21:42.897
What's the matter?

00:21:43.273 --> 00:21:45.859
You looked like you spaced out
for a moment.

00:21:47.193 --> 00:21:48.403
Shut up!

00:21:49.113 --> 00:21:50.740
<i>What just happened...?</i>

00:21:51.324 --> 00:21:52.700
<i>I swore I was...</i>

00:21:53.742 --> 00:21:54.743
<i>Screw it.</i>

00:21:55.827 --> 00:21:57.954
<i>I don't have time to think.</i>

00:21:58.163 --> 00:22:00.790
<i>Right now,
I need to focus on this battle!</i>

00:22:04.211 --> 00:22:05.755
<i>Kenpachi Zaraki...</i>

00:22:06.547 --> 00:22:07.923
<i>You will not die.</i>

00:22:08.590 --> 00:22:10.343
<i>Each time you're on
the verge of death,</i>

00:22:10.343 --> 00:22:11.469
<i>you grow stronger.</i>

00:22:12.303 --> 00:22:16.015
<i>That is the flaw
you put upon yourself.</i>

00:22:16.598 --> 00:22:17.599
<i>And it is also...</i>

00:22:19.059 --> 00:22:20.435
<i>my sin.</i>

00:22:28.402 --> 00:22:31.404
<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:22:31.571 --> 00:22:35.701
<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:35.701 --> 00:22:40.163
<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:40.288 --> 00:22:44.460
<i>We lie buried as we glare
into the distance</i>

00:22:44.794 --> 00:22:47.421
<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:22:47.546 --> 00:22:50.673
<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:22:50.799 --> 00:22:53.176
<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:22:53.301 --> 00:22:55.136
<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:22:55.136 --> 00:22:56.221
<i>Touching</i>

00:22:56.346 --> 00:22:59.724
<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:22:59.724 --> 00:23:03.061
<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:03.186 --> 00:23:09.442
<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:23:09.818 --> 00:23:13.446
<i>It cannot be undone
and cannot be stopped</i>

00:23:13.571 --> 00:23:16.784
<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:23:16.991 --> 00:23:21.663
<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:21.788 --> 00:23:23.833
<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:23:24.040 --> 00:23:25.334
<i>Take everything</i>

00:23:25.334 --> 00:23:30.088
<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:30.213 --> 00:23:32.133
<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:23:32.258 --> 00:23:34.009
<i>Along with our world</i>

00:23:35.094 --> 00:23:38.346
<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:38.471 --> 00:23:44.728
<i>The furthest reaches are now
visible to us</i>

00:23:44.728 --> 00:23:46.814
<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:46.939 --> 00:23:48.731
<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:48.857 --> 00:23:52.236
<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:24:00.243 --> 00:24:02.203
<i>"Battle is everything."</i>

